        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Temperature Controls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Temperature is the most commonly exposed generation parameter in LLM chat interfaces. It scales the model's token probability distribution before sampling: low values make the output deterministic and focused; high values introduce randomness and creativity. Exposing it through a UI control lets users match output style to their task without requiring technical knowledge of the underlying mechanism."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Temperature effect on token probability distribution: low (peaked), mid (balanced), high (flat/entropy)",
          "title": null
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What Temperature Actually Does"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Before a model samples the next token, it produces a vector of logits (raw scores) over the vocabulary. Temperature divides each logit by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "T",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " before the softmax, which controls how peaked or flat the resulting probability distribution is."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef softmax_with_temperature(logits: np.ndarray, temperature: float) -> np.ndarray:\n    if temperature == 0:\n        # Greedy: always pick the highest-probability token\n        probs = np.zeros_like(logits, dtype=float)\n        probs[np.argmax(logits)] = 1.0\n        return probs\n    scaled = logits / temperature\n    exp = np.exp(scaled - np.max(scaled))   # subtract max for numerical stability\n    return exp / exp.sum()\n\n# Example: 4-token vocabulary\nlogits = np.array([3.0, 1.5, 0.8, 0.2])\nprint(softmax_with_temperature(logits, 0.1))  # [0.998, 0.002, 0.000, 0.000] — near-greedy\nprint(softmax_with_temperature(logits, 0.7))  # [0.782, 0.161, 0.049, 0.009] — focused\nprint(softmax_with_temperature(logits, 1.5))  # [0.524, 0.280, 0.142, 0.054] — diverse\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Temperature "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "0",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " effectively disables sampling (greedy decoding). The Anthropic API accepts values from 0 to 1; values above 1 are not supported because they introduce instability (coherence degrades rapidly past 1)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sampling Parameters: Temperature, top_p, top_k"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Temperature is one of three common sampling controls. They interact, so exposing all three without context overwhelms users. Most applications expose temperature only."
          }
        ]
      },
